Feature: against an unreachable broker, bc-container launch exits non-zero, names the broker address, and withholds the startup prompt

  SB-5 readiness-fail arm (PDR-017 §3 SB-5; ADR-028 D1/finding 5). The negative half of
  the composed readiness gate exercised against the real fleet: when the messaging
  database is reachable but the real broker is down, launch must fail closed — it does
  not present an engaged-but-broken agent that discovers the breakage mid-work on every
  brokered request. Lead-owned integration check against the real broker.

@scenario_hash:2264ddea33fe67d4 @lead_integration:agent-vault-broker
  Scenario: launch exits non-zero and withholds the startup prompt when the broker is unreachable
    Given the messaging postgres is reachable on the shopsystem network
    And the agent-vault broker on the shopsystem network is not reachable
    And no BC container named "bc-shopsystem-messaging" is running
    When bc-container launch is run with BC name "shopsystem-messaging" and a startup prompt
    Then the command exits non-zero
    And the failure names the broker's configured address on the shopsystem network
    And no startup prompt has been sent to the tmux session named "agent" in container "bc-shopsystem-messaging"
